Commentary: Quiet start. Full and around off, watchfully defended down to the bowler.
Similar ball, this is defended towards mid on.
FOUR! First runs in this historic Test! Loosener from Abbas. Not quite warmed up yet. Full and on the pads, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket. Easy pickings.
Better, in the old corridor of uncertainty, outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms.
Full and around middle, DK looks to flick again but the ball swings in, goes off the inner half and finds the gap at square leg. By the time fine leg can get across, two runs are taken.

Misfield from Naseem. Full and down the leg side, Karunaratne flicks it behind square leg. Naseem comes charging in from fine leg, gets to the ball but then, looks up, taking his eyes off for a second. That is enough for a mistake to be committed. He fumbles and the batsmen take the third.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Karunaratne keeps it out.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Shaheen. Full delivery on the pads, Dimuth flicks it easily towards fine leg for a boundary.
Outside off, the skipper offers no shot to this one.
Again outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne taps it towards the off side and takes a quick single.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot towards mid on.
Full delivery on off, Dimuth looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, the skipper blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and just outside off, Karunaratne lets it go.
Length delivery on leg, Dimuth flicks it through square leg for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but misses it due to the late movement on this one.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on off, Dimuth plays it to point.
Outside off, the skipper shoulders arms to this one.
Again outside off, Karunaratne lets it go.

FOUR BYES! Wild, very wild from Abbas. He sprays this down the leg side, Oshada looks to flick but cannot get any bat on it. The ball pitches and then swings further away from Rizwan who dives to his left but in vain. The ball races to the fine leg fence.
On a good length on middle, Oshada tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on off, Fernando blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls it down the leg side, Fernando looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Oshada defends it off the back foot.

Massive shout for LBW! No, says umpire Gough. Abbas is not too much interested in the review. Full and outside off, 129.6 kph, coming in, Oshada gets a big stride and then shoulders arms. The ball hits his pads and up go all the Pakistan players, asking the question. Impact does not matter in this case as Fernando is not offering a shot. But perhaps it was not coming back enough to hit the stumps. One of the rare good deliveries this morning.
On a good length on off, Dimuth plays it to covers.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to poke at it but misses it.

FOUR! That is a wonderful shot. Full delivery on middle, perhaps a bit too straight from the angle of the left-armer from over the wicket, Karunaratne walks across a touch, covers the line and flicks it through wide mid on for a boundary.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Dimuth defends it out.
On a good length on off, the skipper blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Oshada defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Fernando keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Fernando plays it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Oshada drives it to mid on.
Full again on off, Oshada drives it to covers.
Good ball to end the over. Outside off, fuller in length, Fernando shoulders arms to this one. The ball then moves a mile, but after it goes past the stumps. The slip cordon likes that.
Bowls a bouncer, Karunaratne does well to duck under it.
On a good length and outside off, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, the skipper defends it out.
On a good length and outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth drives it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne plays it towards point. The batsmen cross ends.

Terrific nut. Now, the ball is taking. Now, the seamers are awake. This is the ball with which Usman gets wickets in white-ball cricket. Full and outside off, Karunaratne walks across, looking to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. Usman appeals as he sees the batsman falling over but the umpire is unmoved. Probably going down the leg side. Yup, Ball Tracker confirms it to be going past the leg stump.
Hit on the pads again. On a good length on leg, Karunaratne looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.

FOUR! The plan is set for that leg-side flick shot but Karunaratne has gone up and over. Not a bad ball at all. Plenty of swing but the skipper has played it nicely. Full and around middle, swinging in, Dimuth walks across and flicks it in the air. 'CATCH IT!' is the call but the ball is well over the man at square leg.

Full delivery on the pads, Karunaratne flicks it towards fine leg. Naseem Shah in the deep runs to his left, gets to the ball quickly but slips and misfields. Recovers well to stop the boundary and the batsmen pounce on the opportunity to take the second.
On a good length on leg, Dimuth nudges it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne offers a calm defense on this one.
Afridi bowls a good length ball on off, Fernando looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Full delivery on off, Oshada drives it to mid off.
On a good length on off, Fernando looks to play it off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good ball! A yorker outside off, Oshada looks to dig it out but is comprehensively beaten.
On a good length and outside off, Oshada does not bother to play at that.
Full delivery on leg, Fernando looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. It goes towards the leg side.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Dimuth blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne keeps it out.
Outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Karunaratne drives it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.

On a good length on leg, Karunaratne looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen change ends. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Full and swinging into Karunaratne, Dimuth defends it to the leg side off the front foot.
Fuller in length and on off, Dimuth looks to work it to the leg side but wears it on his thigh pad.
Length and around off, Karunaratne flicks it to mid on.
Good length and around off, driven straight to the man at covers.
Tap and run. This is the way you play Test cricket. Shaheen bowls full and on the pads, Karunaratne pushes it to mid-wicket and hares to the other end.
Around off, solidly blocked off the back foot by Fernando.

Huge appeal for LBW again! The umpire is unmoved. Shinwari is making Karunaratne dance to his tunes. He is getting good shape into the left-hander. He brings the ball in and Karunaratne is late in his flick shot as the ball hits him on the pads. An appeal goes up but the umpire shakes his head. Usman has a look at his skipper Azhar Ali who comes down for a chat. They are not too keen about the review but would not matter. Before they can take a call, they are timed out. The Ball Tracker later shows that the impact was in line but the wickets was umpire's call.
Full and outside off, swinging in, Karunaratne works it towards mid-wicket.
A short ball now, Dimuth swivels and plays the pull nicely, well in control, all along the ground, through square leg. Two runs taken.
Landed outside off, pushed straight to point.

OUT, BOWLED! Wait, the bails do not fall! Full and outside off, Karunaratne gets across and shoulders arms. The ball comes back in a long way and there is a noise as the ball goes past the pad. The bowler and keeper look to have a chat, as they feel it has hit the pad. Was the ball not doing enough to hit the stumps? Oh dear... here comes the replay. Ball has hit the off stump, but the bail has been rooted to the sticks!
Full and around off, coming in, pushed towards mid on.

Finally Oshada Fernando is off the mark on the 20th ball he has faced. Though a risky one. Fernando won't mind it. Fernando works this length ball to the leg side and calls for a quick single. The fielder there pounces on the ball and throws it towards the non-striker's end. This time the bails come off but Fernando was well in.
BEATEN! This time Shah bowls in the corridor of uncertainty. Dimuth looks to lay bat on ball but misses it as the ball goes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Length and on off, defended to the off side.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and around off, Oshada defends watchfully.
Full and around off, Karunaratne looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge onto his pads and deflects to the leg side. A run taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Length and around off, blocked off the back foot to the bowler.

FOUR! That is such a good shot. Sweet timing there. This should get the batsman going. He bowls one on a length and around off, Fernando drives it through mid off and the ball races to the long off fence.
Length and around off, driven through covers. The batsmen take a couple.
Length and on off, defended to mid on off the front foot.

BYE! Shah bowls one outside off and on a fuller length, Dimuth lets it go through. The ball fails to bounce and goes in between the keeper's legs towards fine leg. A bye is signalled as the batsmen cross ends.
Good length and on off, defended to mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Fernando hops and defends it to the leg side.
Another back of a length ball on off, Fernando once again defends it unconvincingly to the leg side.
Length ball on off, defended off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
Length and on off, Karunaratne looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads.

FOUR! Creamed. Nice way to bring up the 50-run stand. Karunaratne can play through the off side too. Full and outside off, Dimuth leans and drives it through the covers. Not a soul moves. This is a good solid start, though one feels that half the battle was won at the toss itself.
Around off, defended from the crease.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Down the leg side, flicked through fine leg for a run.
Full and around off, watchfully defended towards cover.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne defends it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, the skipper does not bother to play at that.
FOUR! Easy pickings for the skipper. Full delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.

OH! That was nasty! Karunaratne is on the ground. A sharp bouncer from Naseem, Dimuth looks to duck under it but the ball does not bounce as much as he thought it would. Gets hit on the helmet. It goes towards the gully region where the fielder takes the catch. Naseem straightaway starts to celebrate but then realizes that the batsman is in a bit of a bother. Asks the opposition skipper whether he is okay and umpire Kettleborough immediately calls for the physio to come out.
Full delivery on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Full again on off, Oshada drives it past the bowler towards mid off.
On a good length on middle, Fernando flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Fernando tucks it to mid-wicket.

Short and outside off, Fernando cuts it towards point where Shinwari misfields and it goes through him. Shan Masood chases it from cover and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Oshada keeps it out.

The leg stump is missed by a whisker! Wow. Things are slowly starting to happen. Excellent bowling too. Reads the batsman's mind, anticipating that Karunaratne would be expecting a bouncer, given that he got hit an over ago. But the length is a fuller one which takes Dimuth by surprise. He is late, as he is deep inside the crease and makes a tentative push towards cover. The ball, as a result, exposes the gap between bat and pad. Almost sneaks through but takes the inside edge and whizzes past the leg stump towards fine leg. A run taken.
Full delivery on middle, Fernando drives it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Bowls a bouncer on leg stump, the skipper does well to duck under it.
BEATEN! Are we seeing the aftereffects of the hit on the head? Short and outside off, Dimuth looks to chase this delivery but misses it. No feet movement at all.
On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne offers no shot to this one.
Bowls a bouncer, Karunaratne ducks under it.
Length delivery outside off, Fernando taps it to point.
On a length and outside off, Oshada plays it to point.

FOUR! CLASSY! Oshada is slowly getting into his groove now. Full and around off, Fernando drives this pretty straight, thumping into the ground first and then getting it well past mid on. Not straight as an arrow, but straight enough to beat the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Oshada. Pakistan losing their line and length now. Or, they are getting frustrated. Length delivery on the pads, Fernando flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Oshada defends it to point.
FOUR! Not quite off the middle. Full delivery outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but the ball moves away slightly and takes an outside edge. It goes past point for a boundary.
On a good length on off, the skipper defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Dimuth does well to duck under it.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Dimuth punches it to point.
On a good length on middle, the skipper tucks it towards short leg.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Oshada shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Fernando plays it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Oshada blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Oshada plays it to the off side.
On a good length on off, Fernando taps it to point.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.
On a length and outside off, Karunaratne taps it to point.

FOUR! 50 for Dimuth Karunaratne. It is his 24th in Tests. Full delivery outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but gets an outside edge. However, it is played with soft hands. Hence, it goes all along the ground, past a diving second slip, to the third man fence.
On a good length and outside off, Dimuth looks to defend but gets an outside edge on this one. It goes towards third man. The batsmen cross ends.
Full delivery on middle, Oshada drives it to mid on.
Full again on off, Oshada drives it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on middle, the skipper defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dimuth blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne defends it out.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full and outside off, Dimuth drives it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Fernando sweeps it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Oshada drives it through covers. The batsmen take a single.
Floated delivery on off, Dimuth keeps it out.
Tossed up on leg, Karunaratne comes down the track, takes it on the full and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

SIX! Ahahaha! We are seeing the first maximum of the match! Amazing shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Fernando comes down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for a biggie. Perhaps this will be the last over before the break now.

Short delivery outside off, Oshada makes room and cuts it through point for a single. Pakistan fielders anxiously look at Kettleborough, hoping for one more over but he takes the bails off. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
On a good length on off, Fernando drives it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Oshada drives it to covers.
Outside off, Fernando shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Oshada drives it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Oshada defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Oshada leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne taps it to point.
On a length on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Oshada shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer on the leg side, Oshada lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne defends it to mid on off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, the skipper taps it to covers.
On a good length on off, Dimuth defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Karunaratne drives it straight back towards the bowler.
Full again on middle, Dimuth drives it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery outside off, Fernando drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Oshada keeps it out.
Length delivery on middle, Fernando flicks it towards square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne punches it to point.
Length delivery outside off, Karunaratne taps it through point. The batsmen take a single.

OUT! LBW! Sri Lanka lose one of their two reviews. Finally the hosts get the breakthrough. They have been made to toil hard for it but jubilation in the end for the fans and the players. Shaheen once again is the man with the wicket. Shaheen bowls a very full ball on middle. Dimuth looks to defend but he misses and the ball hits him low on the pads. The Sri Lankan skipper opts to take it upstairs. Replay rolls in and though it looks like it might be missing the stumps, Ball Tracker shows all reds and Karunaratne has to walk back. Big wicket for Pakistan. Karunaratne was looking set for a big one but he departs. Can this inspire the hosts who have been timid so far in this Test?
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Mendis lets it go.
Outside off, Mendis shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Mendis drives it to mid off.
Outside off, Kusal shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on leg, Mendis looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen change ends.
On a good length on middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Mendis shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Kusal defends it out.
Length ball around off, Mendis solidly blocks it off his back foot.

Beauty! This is a very good ball by young Naseem. He steams in and bowls it on a length. He holds it with a good seam position. The ball shapes away from the batter. Mendis looks to defend but gets beaten. Lucky not to edge that as that was not far away from the outside edge.
This time Mendis does not even try to defend this length ball outside off.

FOUR! Nicely placed. Good length ball around off, Oshada opens the face of the bar in the last minute and strokes in the gap wide of gully for a boundary. After initially taking it very slow, he is starting to score more consistently.
On a good length on leg, Mendis looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads.
On a length on middle, Fernando flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.
Full delivery on off, Mendis drives it towards covers where Azhar Ali dives and makes a fine stop. The batsmen still manage to take a single.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Oshada watches it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Fernando drives it back towards the bowler.

This stayed low. Mendis is lucky to survive that. Length ball on off, Kusal looks to defend but the ball keeps low. He is quick enough to bend his back and gets some bat on it. It hits the inner half of his bat and onto the pads. Is this the sign of the pitch breaking down or just an odd ball?
Good length delivery on off, Kusal defends it to covers.
Bowls a bumper, Mendis easily ducks under it.
Play and a miss! Good length delivery outside off, Mendis looks to defend but misses it.
Full delivery on middle, Kusal flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good ball but also a very good leave. Good length delivery outside off, it shapes back in. Mendis is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone. The ball just about misses the stump there.
On a good length on leg, Oshada looks to flick but it goes off his thigh pad. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Good length delivery on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Kusal taps it to point.
On a length and outside off, Kusal plays it to covers.
On a good length on off, Mendis plays it to covers.
Good length delivery on middle, Kusal defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Oshada drives it to mid off.
FOUR! Uppish but safe. Full around off, Oshada drives it but it goes off the outer half of his bat over covers. He stays true with the shot and hence the ball clears the infield for a boundary.

OUT! Caught! Naseem has the last laugh. Both the openers back in the hut. The young pacer is ecstatic. Naseem after being hit for a boundary in the previous ball, hits the deck hard around off. It is in the channel of uncertainty. Oshada has a poke at it but gets surprised by the movement. The ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to the man at first slip. Haris Sohail there makes no mistake. After being lethargic in the first session, Pakistan are finding joy in this session.
Outside off, Mathews offers no shot to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Mathews lets it go.
Length delivery on middle, Angelo tucks it to short leg.
Good length delivery on off, Mendis keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Kusal punches it to point.
FOUR! Good shot. Length delivery outside off, Mendis taps it through point for a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Kusal blocks it well.
On a length on off, Kusal plays it to point.

Ohh! Almost the second for Naseem. He is making the ball talk now. Fuller on middle and off, Mathews looks to flick it but the ball goes off the leading edge. Angelo plays it with soft hands and hence the ball does not carry to the man at third slip. Ohhs and ahhs from the Pakistan players. Right now Naseem has his tail up and he would be eager to add one more to his account.
Length delivery on off, Angelo punches it towards point. The batsmen take a run.
Outside off, Mathews does not bother to play at that.
Good length delivery on middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Good leave by Kusal Mendis. On a good length and outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Mendis flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on leg, Mendis flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, Angelo lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Mendis looks to defend but gets an edge on this one. It goes towards the slip region.
Length delivery on off, Mendis taps it through point. The batsmen take a run.
Good length delivery on off, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Mathews keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Mathews punches it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Angelo does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on off, Kusal defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Mendis drives it to mid on.
Length delivery on middle, Mendis pulls it towards square leg for a run.
On a length on off, Mathews taps it to point.
Length delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Kusal shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Mendis looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Kusal offers no shot to this one.

OUT! Caught! Debut Test wicket for Usman Shinwari and he deserves every bit of it. He was unlucky in his first spell but this time he has a wicket to his name. He has persisted with the off pole line and that has reaped its reward. Slightly fuller outside off, he comes wide of the crease. The ball straightens up after pitching. Kusal Mendis strides forward to defend but ends up getting a thick outside edge and goes straight into the mitts of the keeper. Rizwan takes an easy-peasy. Usman Shinwari is up in celebration. A wicket he will never forget. Third bowler to get into the wickets column. Pakistan have their tail up now.

EDGED AND FOUR. Fuller on off, Angelo looks to defend but the ball shapes away just a tad. It takes the outside edge of Mathews' bat. It goes all along the ground through the vacant gully region for a boundary. The key there was he played it with soft hands.
Outside off, Angelo lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Mathews looks to defend but gets an inside edge on it. It goes towards the leg side.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it towards mid-wicket where the substitute fielder Yasir Shah does well to stop it with a dive.
On a good length on leg, Mathews looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, Chandimal shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal plays it to mid on off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Dinesh drives it to covers.
Good length delivery on middle, Chandimal blocks it well.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to covers.
Length delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Mathews taps it towards point. The batsmen take a single.

OUT! Bowled! Abbas now with the wicket. All four pacers have a scalp to their name. Beautiful ball this. A perfect seam bowler's wicket. Good length ball on middle and off, Chandimal looks to defend but the ball moves away off the seam and squares Dinesh all ends up. It hits the top of off stump. Abbas is jumping up and screaming in joy. Poor from Chandimal as well, his feet never moved and Sri Lanka after a good start are falling like a pack of cards.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya tucks it to mid-wicket.
Dhananjaya is off the mark. Lose ball from Abbas. It is on the pads, Mathews glances it towards fine leg and gets a couple to get off the mark.
Outside off, Dhananjaya does not go chasing after it.
Length delivery on off, Mathews defends it towards cover.
Full on off, Mathews flicks it to the right of mid off. The fielder there dives on that side and saves runs for his side.
On a good length on off, Mathews plays it to point.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Mathews does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Angelo defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Dhananjaya leaves it alone.
Bowls it down the leg side, Dhananjaya looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Angelo flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full again on middle, Mathews drives it to mid on.
NO BALL! Shaheen oversteps! Length delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, de Silva plays it to mid on.
Bowls a bouncer, Dhananjaya ducks under it.
Short delivery outside off, Mathews cuts it to point.
On a good length on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Angelo leaves it alone.

FOUR! Finally the barrage of dot balls comes to an end. Poor effort from Naseem. Slightly overpitched on middle, Mathews leans forward and drives it past mid on. Naseem Shah there is late and lazy in his dive and the ball goes past him to the fence.
On a good length on off, Mathews plays it to point.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Dhananjaya shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, de Silva keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya drives it to mid on.
Full again on middle, Dhananjaya plays it towards mid on where Azhar Ali picks the ball and goes for a direct hit at the bowler's end but misses it. The batsmen still take a single.

Ohh... almost had the fifth one there. Smart bowling this from Shaheen. He takes the pace off the ball and bowls a slower one on off. Mathews is outfoxed by it and ends up flicking it uppishly but luckily that falls in no man's land away from the man at short mid-wicket. Dramatic way to end the session. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Starts the session with a yorker wide outside off, Mathews jams it out to the left of the bowler.
Another very full ball, this time on middle. Angelo digs it out towards the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Mathews does not fiddle with it.
Fullish ball on middle and off, defended by Mathews.

Good cricket all round! A full ball wide outside off, Mathews creams it towards the cover region. Imam-ul-Haq there dives to his left and saves at least a couple of runs for his side. Lively start to the session here.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Good length ball on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Usman goes full now on off. Dhananjaya pushes it to mid off.
Once again it is full on off, Dhananjaya once again pushes it to mid off.
Good length delivery on off. Dhananjaya once again blocks it with a dead bat.
Hits the deck hard on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Changes his line and goes full again. Dhananjaya pushes it to mid off. Maiden first up for Shinwari in the last session.
Full delivery on off, Mathews drives it uppishly towards mid off.
Full again on off, Angelo drives it to mid off.
Length delivery outside off, Mathews punches it to point.
Outside off, Mathews shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Mathews leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Mathews flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Length delivery on leg, Dhananjaya looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews drives it to mid on.
Full again on off, Mathews drives it to covers.
Outside off, Dhananjaya does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on middle, de Silva defends it towards mid on off the back foot.
NO BALL! Afridi oversteps! Length delivery on off, de Silva taps it to covers.
FOUR! Good shot by de Silva! Length ball just outside off, Dhananjaya makes room and cuts it behind point for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. Short and outside off, Dhananjaya cuts it hard through point for a boundary. Sri Lanka getting a move on.
On a good length on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Length delivery on middle, Mathews pulls it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Mathews flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. 150 up for Sri Lanka.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Bowls a bouncer, de Silva does well to duck under it.

Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya drives it uppishly towards covers where the fielder does well to stop it but it goes through him. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a length on off, Mathews plays it to point.
On a length on middle, Mathews tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single. The fielder goes for a direct hit at the bowler's end but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, de Silva defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Almost chopped on! Good length ball outside off, Dhananjaya looks to punch it on the off side. He goes hard at it and ends up getting an inside edge on it. De Silva is a lucky man as the ball misses the stumps and goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Short delivery on middle, Dhananjaya pulls it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.

FOUR! Poor fielding from Naseem again. Full on middle, Mathews drives it through mid on. Naseem Shah at mid on is slow to react as the ball goes right between his legs. Shaheen Afridi gives it a chase and looks to pull it back but he fails to do so. He also ends up going down awkwardly on his back.
FOUR! Pulled away with disdain. Short ball on off, Mathews is quick to get on his back foot and hammer his pull through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, AM after scoring two back-to-back boundaries defends it this time with calmness.
Back of a length on off, Mathews keeps it out. Good over for Sri Lanka. 9 runs off it.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it to covers.
Full delivery on off, de Silva drives it to point.
Full again on off, Dhananjaya drives it to mid off.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, de Silva offers no shot to this one.
On a length and outside off, Dhananjaya plays it to point.

Poor bounce allows them to take a single. Full on off, Mathews glances it to the right of mid on. Abbas there gets down to stop it but ends up misfielding as the ball comes to him at an awkward bounce.
FOUR! Runs coming thick and fast for the visitors now. Overpitched on the pads, Dhananjaya has no issues flicking it with power through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Dhananjaya pushes it to cover.
Fuller on off, Dhananjaya drives it straight to short extra cover.
Around off, Dhananjaya defends it towards point.

FOUR! Well struck shot this from Dhananjaya. Overpitched on middle, Dhananjaya smashes it to the left of mid on. Abbas there dives but cannot do much about it as the ball goes past him and to the fence. Brings up the 50-run stand in style.
On a good length on off, Mathews blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo defends it out.
That stayed low. On a good length on middle, Mathews does well to block it.
Short delivery on off, Mathews cuts it to point.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Mathews tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, Dhananjaya plays it to point.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, de Silva looks to cut but misses it.
BEATEN AGAIN! Beauty of a delivery. Good length delivery just outside off, Dhananjaya looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good length ball around off, Dhananjaya plays it wide of gully with an educational edge and fetches himself a boundary. Smart batting this from De Silva.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it towards the leg side. The batsmen take a single.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya looks to guide but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya offers a solid defense on this one.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya plays it to point.
On a length on middle, de Silva flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Good length delivery on off, Mathews defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it through square leg. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Outside off, Mathews shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Mathews drives it to mid off.

OUT! Edged and gone! We have just been joined by Predicto Praky here in the commentary zone and his favourite player has been dismissed. Can watch him for hours tirelessly. Sadly, he will have to watch his exit now. But what a rash shot. For hours, nothing seems to happen in this Test and all of a sudden, someone plays a poor shot and a wicket falls. Pace has done the trick. A length ball outside off, Mathews looks to punch it on the up but is beaten by pace. The ball zips through, takes the outside edge and flies at a good height to second slip where Asad Shafiq takes it nicely. The 62-run stand has been broken.

FOUR! Dickwella is off the mark. Not in the most convincing fashion but he won't mind. On the pads, Dickwella looks to flick but the ball goes off the inside edge fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Outside off, Dickwella lets it go.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Dhananjaya keeps it out.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya looks to drive but misses it.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya taps it to point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
The batsman drives this through the covers. The batsmen have picked up a couple of runs.
On a good length on off, Dickwella plays it to the off side.
FOUR! Good length ball on off, Dickwella gets on his front foot and drives it cleanly through covers for a boundary.
On the pads, Dickwella glances it towards fine leg for a single.
Around the pads, Dhananjaya flicks it fine down the leg side and gets a couple.
Length ball around off, Dhananjaya dabs it to gully.
On a good length on middle, Dickwella tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Dickwella offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Niroshan defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Dickwella plays it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Niroshan defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it to mid-wicket.

Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya looks to flick but misses it and gets hit high on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Ball Tracker shows that it would have missed the stumps.
Outside off, de Silva does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya blocks it well.
Good length delivery on off, de Silva defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya drives it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Dickwella blocks it off the back foot.
Abbas starts with a good length ball closer to the off pole. Dickwella lunges forward and defends it towards cover.
This one is on middle on a length. Dickwella stays on the back foot and taps it towards the on side.
Goes wide of the crease and tries to angle the ball in. It lands outside off and then comes back in. However, Dickwella has his timbers covered as he allows the ball to go the keeper.
Landed around off, Dickwella pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off and middle, Dickwella looks to drive but it goes to mid on off the inner half of the bat. Tight start from Abbas.
FOUR! Beautifully driven! An overpitched ball outside off, de Silva gets in the position and creams it through the covers for first boundary of the day.
On off, de Silva keeps it out.
Around off on a length. Dhananjaya defends it out.
Fullish and on middle, de Silva gets his bat down in time to defend.
Fuller again and on off, de Silva drives it well but straight to mid off.
Overpitched again and outside off too. Dhananjaya leans and drives it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Around off and on a length, Dickwella lunges and defends it out.
Good length ball on off, Dickwella is solid in his defense again.
Slightly shortish around off, pushed towards cover.
Fuller ball outside off, Dickwella drives it through cover-point and picks up a brace.
Beaten! A cutter from Abbas. Dickwella pokes at it to get beaten. Because of the pace variation from Abbas, the ball died well ahead of Rizwan.
Almost dragged on! Shortish ball just outside off, Dickwella looks to cut but gets an inside edge which goes just past the stumps and towards fine leg for a single.
Slightly short and outside off, Dickwella taps it through point for a single.
On off, de Silva gets behind the line to defend.
On off, pushed towards point.
Shortish and around off, de Silva rides the bounce and defends it towards cover.
Full and on off, de Silva drives but can't beat the cover fielder who tumbles to his left to field.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander, de Silva tucks it behind square leg to take a single and keep the strike.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, de Silva keeps it out.
On a length on middle, de Silva flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short delivery outside off, Dhananjaya punches it through point. Usman Shinwari chases it, slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length delivery on off, Dickwella plays it towards the off side of the front foot.
On a good length on off, Niroshan defends it out.

NOT OUT! It bounced just in front of the keeper before getting into the mitts. A good length ball outside off, asking de Silva to go for the drive. He obliges but manages an outside edge which goes behind. Rizwan behind the wicket pouches it diving forward and celebrates along with the bowler. The umpire is not sure if that carried so they get together and call for TV umpire for the assistance. The third umpire checks various angles which confirm that it bounced before getting into the gloves of the keeper there. So, de Silva survives.

50 for Dhananjaya de Silva. It is his 6th Test fifty. Full delivery on leg, Dhananjaya flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple. This has been an excellent innings from him. He will look to convert this into a big one.
Bowls a bouncer, de Silva sways away from it.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery outside off, de Silva looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off, Dhananjaya shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Dickwella defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Dickwella offers a back foot defense on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Niroshan defends it out.
On a good length on off, Niroshan guides it to third man.
Full delivery outside off, Dickwella drives it to covers.
Outside off, Niroshan leaves it alone.
Outside off, Dhananjaya offers no shot to this one.
Again outside off, de Silva lets it go.
On a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya does not bother to play at that.
Outside off, de Silva shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards backward point for a boundary.
Outside off, de Silva leaves it alone.
Sohail starts with a loopy ball on middle, Dickwella tucks it towards square leg.
This one is on middle, Dickwella pushes it towards mid-wicket.
On middle, it is defended.
Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. A full ball on the pads, Dickwella looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the pad. A stifled appeal from the bowler but the umpire is not interested.
Flighted one on middle, Dickwella sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Shortish and outside off, de Silva punches it through covers for a single.
Shafiq starts with a ball around off, de Silva looks to drive but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes towards long on.
Fires this on the pads, de Silva flicks it behind square leg for a couple.
Down the leg side this time. Dhananjaya lets it be.
Flatter and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Another one on the stumps line, it is defended.
Fires this just outside off, de Silva looks to nudge it towards third man but the keeper does well to field by diving to his right.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dickwella defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Dickwella looks to play the reverse sweep but gets hit on the pads.
Floated delivery on off, Dickwella plays a reverse sweep through point. The batsmen cross ends.
Loopy delivery on off, de Silva keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Tossed up and on off, Dickwella is superb playing spin. This time he sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Dickwella plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Floated delivery on off, Dickwella keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Niroshan blocks it well.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dickwella defends it out.
On a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, de Silva plays it to the off side.
Full delivery on off, Dhananjaya drives it to mid off.
Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on leg, Dhananjaya looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

On a length on middle, de Silva looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards square leg. De Silva wants a quick single. The square leg fielder hares at the ball, picks it up and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. However, de Silva has made his ground. However, the ball deflects towards wide of mid off and an extra run is conceded.
Length delivery on leg, Dickwella looks to flick but misses it.
On a length on middle, Dickwella flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Dhananjaya offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Nice shot. Length delivery outside off, Dhananjaya guides it uppishly towards third man for a boundary. 50-run stand is up between Dhananjaya de Silva and Niroshan Dickwella.
On a length on middle, de Silva nudges it towards square leg. The batsmen take a run.
On a length on off, Niroshan plays it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length and outside off, Dickwella taps it to point.
BEATEN! That was close to the off stump! Good length delivery just outside off, Dickwella looks to defend but misses it. It missed the off stump by a whisker.
Length delivery outside off, Dickwella punches it through point. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Niroshan looks to slice but it goes off the outside edge. It goes through point. The batsmen take a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
EDGE AND FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes between second slip and gully towards third man for a boundary.
Full and outside off, Niroshan looks to drive it through the off side but inside edges it onto the pads.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Full delivery on middle, Dickwella flicks it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but misses it as he was late in driving that ball. The ball also swung there.
Length delivery on middle, Dickwella flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, de Silva leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Dickwella defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.

OUT! That is taken and it is Shaheen Afridi who provides the breakthrough! This is a huge scalp. Sri Lanka do not have too much of batting beyond Dilruwan Perera. With the ball still new, they can get into the tail pretty quickly. Full and wide outside off, Dickwella reaches out and slices it through point. It is hard, fast and low to gully but Babar Azam gets low and takes it! Dickwella's watchful innings ends. He was looking to attack the second new ball but is gone now.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery from Afridi. On a good length and outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it due to the inswing on this one.

NOT OUT! Pitched outside leg. Review lost. But cannot really blame Afridi for coaxing his captain. That looked to be umpire's call on height but to the naked eye, did not look like it was pitched outside leg. It was on a length, Dilruwan looked to flick but missed and was hit on the pads. There was a loud appeal but the umpire turned it down. Afridi felt it looked good, but Azhar Ali reckoned it was high. Still, for his bowler, he took the review. Tough luck.
Length delivery on leg, Perera looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a single. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
On a good length on off, Perera plays it to point.
Full delivery on middle, Dilruwan flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on off, Perera drives it through mid off. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it out.
On a good length on off, de Silva keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full delivery on off, Perera looks to drive but gets an inside edge on this one. It misses the stumps and goes towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya plays it back towards the bowler where Shaheen Afridi picks the ball and takes the stumps at the striker's end but no harm done.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, de Silva looks to play inside the line but misses it.
Afridi starts with a shortish length ball just outside off. De Silva taps it towards cover.
This is closer to the off pole and on a good length, Dhananjaya blocks it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Overpitched and outside off, de Silva leans forward and creams it through the covers. First runs and first boundary of the day.
Beaten! In the channel outside off. Dilruwan goes to cut but misses out.
This time he makes a leave as it is again in the corridor outside off.
Good length ball outside off, it shapes away as well. Perera shoulders arms again.
Another leave! Pitches outside off and shapes away again. Perera is not going after these as he missed out on the first one.
Gets closer to off pole. This time Perera is in two minds. He plays in the line to get beaten.
Around off and middle, Perera keeps it out coming forward.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya cuts it to point where the fielder makes a diving stop.
Full delivery on off, Dhananjaya plays it to the off side.
Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya drives it through covers. Azhar Ali chases it, slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Full again on off, Perera plays it towards point for a single.
Full delivery outside off, de Silva drives it through covers again. The batsmen pick up a couple. Dhananjaya moves into the 80s.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it out.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
Full delivery on middle, Perera flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.

That just missed the stumps. On a good length and just outside off, Dhananjaya looks to cut but gets a bottom edge on this one. The ball bounces and he finds where the ball has gone. It just misses the leg stump by a whisker.
Good length delivery on middle, de Silva keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya plays it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Bowls a bouncer, Perera does well to duck under it.
Outside off, Dhananjaya shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on off, Dhananjaya plays it towards point. De Silva wants the single but Dilruwan sends him back.
Outside off, de Silva offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
On a good length on off, Perera looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery outside off, Perera lets it go.
Good length ball just around off, defended well by de Silva.
Around off again, this time de Silva defends it awkwardly. It is very gloomy out there and that might hamper the visibility of de Silva.
FOUR! Nope! No problems it seems for de Silva. Short of a length ball on middle, Dhananjaya rocks back and pulls this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller one outside off, driven towards mid off.
Beaten! Lot of swing on this one. Pitched around off, de Silva looks to feel for it but the ball moves away from him and falls just in front of Rizwan. Well collected by him.
Good zip there! It lands outside off and skids through. Dhananjaya shoulders arms to this one. End of an over which started a couple of days ago.
First run today! A loosener by Abbas. On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Dhananjaya scores his first run today! Slightly shorter and outside off, de Silva pushes it through covers for one.
Edged and short! This is on a length and around off, it pitches and skids through. Dhananjaya defends inside the line, it goes off the outside edge but well short of first slip.
Another length delivery and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard! Up and over the slip cordon! Shorter and outside off, Perera throws his bat at it. It goes off the outside edge and into the third man fence.
Another length ball around off, this one comes back in a little. Dilruwan goes hard at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller length and on off, de Silva defends it to the off side.
Length ball on the pads, de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length and on off, defended with a solid front foot defense.
On a length and on middle, played towards the leg side.
Fuller in length and on the pads, Dhananjaya flicks it through square leg and takes a couple.
FOUR! Shah strays one on the pads and de Silva takes full toll of it as he just helps the ball on its  way through fine leg. The fielder there dives across but fails to prevent the boundary.
On a length and on off, tapped towards the off side.
Beaten! Brilliant delivery for a right-hander. It lands on a length and outside off, just about manages to get it past the forward push of Perera.
Perera looks to flicks this length ball through the leg side but gets an inside edge onto his pads. The ball rills towards leg gully.
Outside off, defended to the off side.

FOUR! Perera is just playing a superb hand here. He this time sees the length early and lofts it through covers. There is a shout of 'Catch it' from the fielder but it is well in the gap as the ball crosses the fence with ease. That also brings up the 300 for Sri Lanka.
Good sensible batting. Perera defends this length ball off the back foot towards the off side.
On a length and around off, Dhananjaya plays it nice and late and onto the ground.
Shorter and on middle, de Silva keeps it out.
Dhananjaya moves onto 97! Fuller and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
This is angled into the pads, Perera looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls on the leg side and leg bye is taken.
That ball has taken the inside edge onto the pads.
BEATEN! A loose shot that. It is way too far outside off, de Silva goes after it away from his body but gets beaten.
Length and on the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.

FOUR! 100 for Dhananjaya Silva! Finally the moment arrives for him. He came out to bat on the first day and gets to his ton on te 5th. He's had to wait, wait and wait due to the weather but finally gets to the milestone which will still be extremely pleasing. His 6th ton in Tests. He gets there by creaming this full delivery through covers. Takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman. One run added to the total.
On off, it is kept out.
On a length and outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, punched off the back foot towards  off side.
Good start for Sri Lanka. Rajitha does not get the swing as he keeps it outside off. Masood lets it go.
Length and around off, defended to the leg side.
On a length and outside off, Masood leaves it by shouldering arms.
Fuller in length and on middle and off, Masood blocks it solidly off the front foot.

Edged and taken! Has he or is it just short? Sri Lanka are claiming it and the umpire takes it upstairs. The SOFT SIGNAL IS NOT OUT! A length delivery around off, it angles away. Masood looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge and towards gully where Perera seems to have taken a low catch. An appeal but the umpire is not sure. He has a chat with the other umpire and then takes it upstairs. Replays roll in and guess what? Rajitha oversteps. No need of moving ahead as it is not a legal delivery. Also, the ball did not carry so it would have remained not out.
A yorker now on off, Masood looks to jam it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, blocked. End of a good first over by Rajitha.
Length and outside off, left alone.
On a length and around off, defended back to the bowler off the full face of the bat.
Abid Ali gets off the mark here. He just clips one off his pads through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Good length and outside off, Ali leaves it alone.

An appeal for LBW! Not given. On a length and around off, Ali looks to defend it to the off side but the ball keeps low and just takes the bottom of the bat. Vishwa Fernanado appeals but the umpire is unmoved. He then looks towards his skipper and Karunaratne calms him down. Replays later show that the decision of the SL skipper was good enough.
On off defended off the back foot.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, Masood strokes it nicely but straight to mid off.
A good bumper this, Masood thinks of pulling it but then it zips through and he lets it be.

OUT! CAUGHT! Masood has been dismissed off a full toss! Rajitha himself can't believe he has struck on that delivery. Also, this time it is a legal ball. Masood slowly walks back and this is the perfect start for the Lankans. Masood creams this but does not keep it down. It goes straight to mid off where Chandimal takes a simple catch.
This is angled into the pads, it is pushed to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Almost another! Full and wide outside off, Abid throws his bat at it away from the body and gets beaten.
Good length and on off, Abid lunges and keeps it out.
Way too wide outside off again, this time Abid lets it be.

That is a beauty! This lands around the leg pole and moves away quite a lot. Abid looks to defend but is beaten. The ball bounces in front of the keeper so he fails to stop it cleanly. A bye is taken.
On off, blocked.
On a length and around off, defended off the back foot by Abid.
Length and outside off, Abid lifts his bat and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Full and on middle, Abid defends it to mid-wicket.
Length and on off, defended to the off side.
Full and on the pads, Abid flicks it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Good length on middle, defended to the leg side.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
FOUR! Up and over! Shorter in length and outside off, Abid throws his bat at it. It goes off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Full and wide outside off, a tempter by Fernando but Ali leaves it.
Fuller and on middle, it is worked against the angle to Ali.
Another leave as it is again bowled outside off.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
On off, defended nicely.
Good length again and on off, Ali keeps it out nicely.
A sharp bumper and on the body, Ali spots it late but ducks under it.
Well played! Just short and around off, extra bounce on this one. Ali does well to play it with soft hands. It goes on the bounce to gully.
Ali is off the mark as he works this one on the pads towards fine leg.
Full and wide of off stump, Azhar looks to squeeze it but the ball just about goes past the outside edge.
FOUR! Brilliantly timed there by the Pakistan skipper. He just leans on and then drives it through covers and the ball goes past the fence.

Confusion and safe in the end. Ali taps one to the point region and the fielder there gets to the ball quickly. Abid Ali calls for the single but his skipper is not interested. Later on Azhar Ali takes off for the run seeing Abid Ali already half way down. The fielder from point has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Also Azhar Ali gets in with a dive. A single taken in the end.
Outside off, left alone.
Another leave as the ball is way outside off.
On a length and on the pads, Abid Ali fails to flick it off his pads. The ball hits the pads and rolls towards the keeper who dives to his left and grabs it.
On off, it is pushed to covers.
Outside off, not played at.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Goes wide of the crease and angles this one into the off pole, blocked.
A good bumper again, Ali ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven back past the bowler but for no runs as mid off gets across quickly.
A little too wide outside off to make the batter play.
The ball is way outside the off stump, easy leave for the batsman.
Another full ball and on middle, it is hit to mid on.
On off, blocked again.
Outside off, left alone.
On the fuller side and on middle, Ali pushes it towards mid on. The fielder there dives to his right but fails to stop it cleanly. A single taken.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket for another single.
Outside off, not played at.
Slower one outside off, not played at.
One more ball on a length, Ali guides it to point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Just wide of second slip. Not sure why there isn't a third slip in place especially when you are looking for wickets. Shorter and outside off, Ali pushes at it away from the body. The ball flies off the outside edge and goes past the diving Mendis at second slip and into the third man fence. Fortunate was Abid there.
A good short one now, Ali ducks under it.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Right off the middle this time! Slightly shorter and outside off, Abid gets on top of the bounce and smashes it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! A hit-me delivery to start with. Short and way too wide outside off, Ali goes back and slaps it through covers for a boundary. A loosener to begin with by Perera and Ali puts it away.
On middle, Ali works it with the turn to mid on.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
A single now as it is flicked through square leg.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is shorter in length and around off, Abid gets on top of the bounce and uses the pace of the bowler. Guides it past point and gets a boundary.
Angled into the batter, defended.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Shot of the day probably! Fuller and on off, Abid shows the full face of the bat and creams it through mid off. Runs coming quickly now.
On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for no runs.
On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, Abid goes back and works it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and on middle, the batter works it to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Gives it air and lands it on off, worked to mid-wicket again.
Short one on the body. Hurrying onto the batsman. Abid pulls it through fine leg and gets to the other end.
On a length and on the pads, Azhar tickles it towards fine leg for a run. 150kph delivery this from Kumara. Really quick there.
Short one Abid ducks under it.
Back of a length and around off, Abid drops his wrists and sways away from the line of the delivery.
Full and angled into the pads, Abid works it towards mid-wicket and crosses ends.
Length and around off, Abid taps it to covers and takes a single.
Tossed up outside off, Abid taps it to point and takes a quick single.
Flighted and on off, defended off the front foot.
Full and on off, Abid brings out the forward block in play.
Flighted and on the pads, Abid works it to the leg side.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Full and on middle, driven through mid on for a run.
Good length and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Length and around off, driven straight to covers.
Short one on the body, Azhar ducks under it with ease.
Around off, tapped towards covers for no run.
FOUR! Lovely cover drive. Azhar Ali drives this fuller one through covers and the ball has enough on it to cross the fence with ease.
Around off, defended off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Abid defends it to the  off side.
50-run stand up between Abid Ali and Azhar Ali. Abid works this tossed up ball off his pads towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Full and on middle, driven straight to mid on.
Once again Azhar drives this full ball to mid on.
Flighted one on off, Azhar drives it through mid on and takes a single.
Abid Ali blocks this tossed up ball around off to the off side. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses. A loosener to start with by the bowler.
Outside off this time, not played at.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone again.
Angled into the pads, Azhar works it down to fine leg and takes one. First run in this session.
Close! This is on middle, Abid flicks it at the very end through square leg for one. He worked that off the stumps, had to get bat to ball or he was a goner.
Fuller in length and on off, Azhar pushes it to mid off.
Flatter and on off, Abid stays back and keeps it out. No turns for the off spinner yet.
Gives it air and lands it on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Another full ball outside off, Abid drives it square on the off side and takes one.
Tossed up on off, Ali lunges and blocks it solidly.
A little too straight, this is worked to the fielder at short fine leg.
On off, blocked.
Length and on the pads, Azhar flicks it through mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full and on the pads, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket. By the time the fielder in the deep can clean it up the batsmen take a couple.

An appeal for LBW from the Sri Lankans. The umpire is unmoved. This is bowled on a length and around off, Azhar Ali looks to defend it but is late in bringing his bat down and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads. The bowler and the slip fielders appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Right call there from the umpire.
Length and outside off, Azhar  guides it towards point.
Full and on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for a run.
Length and on off, Azhar defends it from within the crease.
Azhar Ali gets a run off the misfield. Perera bowls one on off, Azhar drives it towards covers where the fielder misfields and allows the batsmen to cross ends.
Abid pushes this tossed up ball to covers.
Tossed up outside off, Abid guides it through point for a single.
On off, defended to the off side.
Around off, driven back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, defended to the off side.
Short stuff and almost a wicket there. Abid pulls it uppishly and the ball just about manages to evade the leaping mid-wicket fielder. The batsmen get a couple.
Length and on off, driven to covers.
Good length and on off, driven once again to covers.

FOUR! Overpitched and it gets what it deserved. Fernando goes full and invites Abid to drive. Abid there obliges and drives it through mid off and the ball races past the diving mid off fielder towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Length and around off, pushed to the off side.
Abid defends this length ball on off by coming right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted ball on off, Azhar keeps it out nicely.
Gives it a lot of air and bowls it on off, Ali strokes it to mid off.
Ali uses his feet and then pushes it to mid on for one.
One more tossed up ball on off, Abid strokes it to mid off.
A single as this is pushed through the off side for one.
Flatter and on off, Ali guides it through point for one.
Outside off, Azhar does not play at it.
One more length ball around off, AA pushes it back to the bowler.
This is angled into the pads, Ali works it towards mid-wicket. It goes through the hands of the fielder and hits his knee. He is in some pain.
A shorter one on the body, Ali pulls it down to fine leg for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up on middle and leg, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Flighted on middle and leg, Abid goes down on one knee and sweeps it very fine and into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, defended off the front foot.
Tossed up and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on leg, tucked to mid-wicket.
Once again Abid sweeps this full ball but fails to get the gap as the ball goes towards square leg.
Just outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Past the fielder and a boundary! This is slightly fuller and around middle, Azhar Ali strokes it towards mid on. The fielder there runs to his left and then dives but fails to stop it.
On off, defended.
Another one on a length, Ali is solid in defense.
Just outside off, the batter need not play at those.
Nice drive but for no runs! Fuller and on off, Ali strokes it to mid off.
Loopy ball around off, Abid defends it onto the ground.
On off, defended again.
Flatter this time but he line is the same, Abid plays it off the back foot.
On middle, this time, AA works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, Abid pushes it towards cover for one. He moves onto 46.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on middle, Ali works it to mid on.
Length and on off, Abid punches it through covers and gets a couple. Just 2 runs away from his maiden Test fifty.
Length and on off, defended to mid on.
Good length and outside off, Abid punches once again but to covers this time.
Full and outside off, Abid looks to squeeze it towards point but fails to middle it as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
BOUNCER! Abid sits under the short ball as it sails over him.

MAIDEN TEST FIFTY! What a knock this has been from him. He has looked calm composed and settled out there through out his innings. Coming onto the delivery it was a back of a length ball outside off, Abid guides it past point and gets couple. He has 100 on ODI debut. Can he score a 100 on Test debut too? Thus becoming the first cricketer to achieve this feat.
Tosses it up on off, it is driven to mid off.
A single as this is worked through mid-wicket.
Another couple! On the pad, Abid Ali works it fine on the leg side and takes an easy two.
On middle, the batter lunges forward and keeps it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated ball on off, Abid strokes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Azhar punches it to covers.
Full and angling in the pads, Azhar defends with his bat pad close to each other.
Length and on off, Azhar defends it to the off side.
Length ball on middle, Azhar drives it towards mid on.

OUT! In the air... taken! End of the stand  that looked ever so comfortable out there. End of Azhar Ali who was looking all set for another big score. Just the breakthrough Sri Lanka needed. A good short one on middle, it rises on the batter. Azhar tries to work it on the leg side but fails to get on top of the bounce. It hits the splice and lobs towards mid-wicket where Karunaratne takes a dolly. The skipper falls after getting off to a start.
Good delivery to welcome Pakistan's best better! This is on a length and around off, it jags back in. Azam looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
BEATEN! Flatter and outside off, Abid looks to cut but the ball goes past the  outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Full and on middle, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the pads, Abid sweeps it through fine leg and gets a couple.

FOUR! Perera tosses one up outside off, Abid cannot control his instincts and he looks to go for the drive. The ball takes the outside edge and flies past the lone slip fielder and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Full and on the pads, Abid flicks it through square leg and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Azam drives it straight to the man at mid off.
A bumper and on middle, ducked under.
A shot one again, Ali does well to hop and defend it.
One more short one and on off, it is defended.
Length and around off, this is guided to point.
Fuller and on middle, Ali strokes it to mid on.
On off, Ali stays back and keeps it out comfortably.
Tossed up on off, Babar defends it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted and on off, Babar defends it to point.
Flighted and on off, Babar defends it to point.
Tossed up on off, driven through point for a run.
Perera gives this one more air and bowls it on middle. Babar drives it towards covers where the fielder mid fields to all a single. 100 up for Pakistan.
Tossed up on middle, Abid drives it towards mid on.
Shorter and on middle, ducked under.

Short! Babar went at that with hard hands! Length and outside off, Babar looks to drive it on the up but it goes off the outside edge and on the bounce to gully. Dilruwan dives and stops it with one hand. He saves a boundary in the end.
Shorter and on off, Azam stands tall and defends it.
A good short one again, Azam spots it early and lets it go over him.
On the fuller side, Azam mistimes his drive towards mid on. His bat turned in his hand there, Kumara is bowling quick here.
Shorter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Floated on off, defended from within the crease.
Tossed up on off, driven back to the bowler.
Flighted and on off, driven through covers for a run.
Floated and on middle, Azam punches the ball to the off side off the back foot.
Flighted and around off, Azam defends it off the front foot and into the ground.

Ohhs and Ahhs! Fortunate enough for Azam here. Perera tosses one up around off and brings the ball back into the right-hander. Babar lifts his bat and the ball just about goes past the off stump. Rather close one and a brave leave too.
Shorter and around off, Abid pushes it wide of deep point and takes two.
Shorter and on off, kept out.
A short one again, this one is well-directed. Ducked under.
On the fuller side, Ali strokes it to mid on.
On off, Azam is solid in defense.
Slightly fuller, Azam strokes it to mid on.
Flatter and on off, blocked.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, it is hit to mid off.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. The batsmen have run through for a single.
FOUR! Exquisite! A full ball outside off, Azam goes against the turn and he creams it through the off side for a boundary.
Pushes it through covers for one.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Babar defends it to covers.
Length and on off, Babar drives it to covers once again.
Bumper! Fernando goes short  and the ball bounces a lot higher over the batsman's head. The umpire calls it a wide.
Full and on the pads, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

Back of a length and outside off, Abid hops onto his toes and punches the ball through covers. The fielder from third man runs across to his right and fields it. The batsmen in the meantime take three.
Back of a length and on off, Babar cuts it through point for a single.
Floated on off, Babar defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Babar looks to flick it to the leg side but gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball goes towards point.
Tossed up on off, kept out easily.
Floated on middle, Babar blocks it towards mid on.
Short and wide of off stump, Babar punches the ball off the back foot through covers for a single.
Flighted ball on off, defended off the back foot to the off side.
Starts off with a loosener! Shorter and outside off, Azam lets it be.
One more short one! This is slapped through covers for one.
On the shorter side again, this is pulled through mid-wicket for one.
A freebie but Azam fails to put it away! Short and on the pads, it is pulled to square leg.
Quicker and outside off, left alone.
Azam misses out on another freebie! A full toss outside off, Azam looks to hit it hard but mistimes it through covers for one.
Tossed up outside off, driven to long on for a single.
Floated and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, worked to short mid-wicket.
Flatter and outside off, punched towards covers for a single.
Tossed up on middle and off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on off, driven towards mid off for a quick single.
Flatter and outside off, Babar slashes it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Shorter and outside off, Abid rocks onto the back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Back to back boundaries. Abid is going along nicely here. Once again he cuts this flatter one outside off througfh point and into fence for boundary.
Tossed up and on off, Abid defends it to point.
Floated on off, Abid drives it through mid off for a run.
Three boundaries in the over. It's all happening here. Babar comes to the party now. He now drives this tossed up ball through covers for a boundary.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Fifty run stand up! This has been a very exciting one. Both have dealt in boundaries and they hit one to get to that landmark. This is tossed up outside off, it is creamed through covers.
On middle, defended.
Shorter and on off, Azam pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Leaking boundaries are the bowlers here! This is another full ball outside off, Azam leans into it and caresses it through covers.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. The batsmen have picked up a couple of runs.
Flatter and outside off, Abid cuts it through point for a single.
Full and on middle, Babar drives it through mid on for a run.
