Flatter and outside off, Abid punches the ball through covers for a couple.
Tossed up on the pads, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the pads, Abid flicks it off his pads to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up on off and middle, Babar defends it off the back foot.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Azam now gets off strike as he eases it down to long on.
Worked with the turn through mid-wicket for one.
Well played in the end! Azam comes down the track but slips. He though does well to defend it out.
Azam keeps strike now as he punches it down to long on.
Flatter and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Too easy! Azam would hit that drive all day long. It is another half volley outside off, Babar strokes it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
On off, this is kept out.
Azam comes down the track and eases it down to long on for one.
Worked through square leg for one.
Another single as another ball is worked on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle and leg, tucked through mid-wicket for a run by Babar.
Tossed up on off, blocked off the front foot.
Flighted one on off, Babar plays the forward defense.
Full and on the pads, Abid looks to tuck it to the leg side but finds the fielder to perfection there.
Floated on middle and leg, Abid works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on the pads, Babar flicks it to the leg side.
Plays the paddle sweep but straight to short fine leg.
Floats it up on off, Abid opens the face of the bat and guides it through point for one.
Loopy ball on middle, Azam lunges and keeps it out.
On middle, it is hit with the turn through mid on for one.
On off, Ali prods forward and keeps it out.
On the pads, Ali works it towards mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Azam pushes it to the man at covers.
Another shorter in length delivery around off, BA stands tall and punches it to covers.
On the off pole this time, the length is a touch fuller. Azam drops it on the off side and takes one.
This is angled into the batter, Azam shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid on.
A good short one, right on the body. Abid works it towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
Tossed up on off, Babar drives it through covers for a run.
Tossed up around middle and leg, defended off the front foot to the leg side.
Floated outside leg, Abid flicks it througjh mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted around off, Azam defends it off the back foot by coming right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Brutally hit. Babar takes a step or two forward on this tossed up ball outside off and drives it straight down the ground. The  ball races to the fence in a flash, Not a single fielder moved. Such was the timing on this shot.
Tossed up on off, Babar drives once again but this time finds mid off.
Shorter and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller this time and on middle, kept out.
A sharp bumper, Azam moves out of the way at the very end.
Another single! Fuller and on middle, it is hit towards mid on for one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Length and outside off, Babar pushes it off the back foot through covers for a single. That will also be TEA ON DAY 5!
Tossed up on middle and leg, tucked to mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Babar drives it through mid on for a run. First one of this session.
Flighted on middle and leg, Abid drives it  back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, defended off the back foot towards the bowler.
Full and on the pads, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
Full and on the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
FOUR! What a way to get to your half ton. He just stands tall on this back of a length delivery and punches it through covers. There is no one in the deep which means the ball meets the ropes.
Length and on off, Babar  defends it to the off side and hares for a quick single.
Length and on the pads, Abid looks to flick it down the leg side but the ball rolls off his pads towards leg slip.
Short one on middle and leg, Abid ducks under it.
Back of a length and on middle and leg, Abid hops inside the crease and defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length and on middle, Abid hops inside the crease and defends it back to the bowler.
Three runs! Nicely played! Brings out the paddle sweep and hits it nice and fine on the leg side for three.
On the stumps, kept out.
Well bowled! This lands on off and goes on with the angle. Abid defends inside the line and gets beaten.
Comes down the track now but gets too close to the pitch of the ball. Mistimes it towards mid off for one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Gives it air and lands it on middle, Azam eases it down to long off for one.
Short one on middle and leg, Babar pulls but finds mid-wicket.
FOUR! 100-run stand up between the two! Shorter in length and on the body, Azam swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Length and on off, Babar mistimes the drives it to mid on.
Short and wide of off stump, Babar just opens his arms and punches the ball through covers. The ball races to the fence without any fuss.
Around off on a length, defended to the off side.
Length ball on off, defended off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Abid defends it off the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, Ali drives it  straight down the ground but the timing is not there. The fielder from long on comes across and fields it. Only a couple results this time.
Tossed up on off, defended to the off side.
Full and on the pads, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
Abid gets close to the pitch of this tossed up ball and then blocks it.
Tossed up on the pads, Abid flicks it off his pads to mid-wicket.
Shorter and around off, this is pushed to covers.
A slower one but down the leg side, it is left alone.
On off, Azam guides it to point.
On the shorter side again, blocked.
One more short ball and on middle, it is evaded.
On the shorter side, Abid pushes it to covers.
Azam makes room and Dhananjaya bangs it short. It is pushed wide of long off for two.
Fires this down the leg side, it is left alone.
FOUR! Azam into the 70s. He is hitting boundaries for fun at the moment. Short and outside off, this is slapped through covers and it races away.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. They pick up a single.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Another one on the pads, this time it is worked wide of mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Abid now on 99! Excellent shot this. It is short and around off, Abid Ali smashes it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.

100 for Abid Ali on debut! A couple to bring it up. An excellent feat, he becomes the first man in the history to score a ton on ODI debut and Test debut. Brilliant. Take a bow young man. Takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause from the big crowd which has come to watch this last day. He gets there by cutting this short ball through covers for two.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Abid goes after it with not a lot of foot movement. He gets beaten.
On the fuller side, this is hit to mid on.
A dot to end as this is hit to mid on.
Tossed up on middle, driven towards lonf on for a run.
Flatter and on off, driven towards covers for a run.
Tossed up on the pads, driven to mid on.
Full and on the pads, Babar sweeps it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Full and on the pads, Abid tucks it to the leg side for a run.
Floated on middle, Azam flicks it to mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Length and outside off, Babar drives it to mid on.

Brilliant fielding in the deep. Vishwa Fernando bowls one on a length and gives a lot of room for Babar to free his arms. Azam there drives it through covers. The fielder from Third man runs to his right and pulls the ball inside the ropes with the dive. The umpire just go for the check whether the fielder was in contact with the ball when he went over the ropes but nothing such thing. A couple is what results.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries. Fernando goes short and Azam rocks onto the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep dives but fails to keep the ball in play as it crosses the fence.
Length and outside off, Azam punches it through the off side for a single.
Abid defends this length ball to the off side.
Back of a length and on off, Abid punches the ball off the back foot.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter in length, Azam fails to get to the pitch of it. He tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good fielding! Brings out the sweep shot and hit sit fine on the leg side. The fielder at short fine leg dives to his right and saves a boundary.
Slower through the air and on middle, blocked.
FOUR! Too short and put away! Azam rocks back and hits it in the gap in the mid-wicket region. A fielder in the deep but he has no chance.
Azam keeps strike as he works this down to long on for one.
Floats it up on middle, Azam strokes it to covers.
On middle, kept out.
Azam misses out there! This is down the leg side, Azam looks to sweep but misses.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Extremely full and on middle, Azam plays it back to the bowler.
A single from the last ball as Azam strokes it down to long off.
On the pads, it is worked to short fine leg.
Full and on off, driven to long off for a run.
Full and on the pads, Abid tucks it to leg gully.

That straighten after pitching. Abid was lining up for a flick though the leg side but the ball spins the other way to take the outside edge. The ball runs past the vacant slip cordon and towards third man. The batsmen have enough time in the world to get back for third.
Floated on off, defended off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up on leg, the ball further spins further down the leg side and Azam misses his flick. The fielder from short fine leg runs behind the ball and fields it. A Bye taken.
On the pads, it is worked to short fine leg.
Comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. It is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is a very good shot! He steps out and also stays leg side of the delivery. Opens the face at the end and guides it through the left of cover for a boundary.
Moves onto 95 with a single as this is pushed through mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
On the stumps, blocked.
Tossed up on off, pushed through mid off and gets on to 96 is Babar here with a single.
Tossed up around off, Abid drives it through covers for a run.
Full and on the pads, Babar flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket for a single. 3 shy of a century is Babar.
Tossed up defended near the pitch on the off side.
Flighted and on off, driven to mid off.
Another floated one on off, Abid drives to mid off.

FOUR! 100 for Babar Azam on his very first innings on home soil. He punches his fist in the air, takes his helmet off and has both his arms aloft. Best batter for Pakistan in recent times without a doubt. Also, it has been a very fluent innings by him. His third ton in Tests. He gets there by slapping this short ball through covers for a boundary.
Flatter and on middle, this is kept out.
Tossed up on off, driven to long on for a run.
Flighted on off, Abid punches the ball off the back foot through the covers for a single.
Tossed up on off, defended off the back foot.
Floated on off, blocked of the back foot.
NO BALL! A rare one from a spinner. Dhananjaya oversteps here! Full and on middle, driven to long on for a run.
Floated one on off, blocked off the front foot.
Babar blocks this one right of the middle of the bat.
Azam works this full ball off his pads to mid-wicket.
Once again Azam plays this tossed up ball on the pads to mid-wicket.
De Silva sprays one down the leg side. Azam looks to lay bat on the ball. He fails and the ball rolls to the short fine leg off the pads.
Full and on middle, Azam defends it off the front foot. That will be it. The players go for the handshakes and that's a DRAW!
